  • Method Details

    • loadFile

      void loadFile​(java.lang.String filePath) throws java.lang.IllegalStateException
      Loads an audio file (only AIFC, AIFF, AU, SND and WAVE formats are supported) to be played.
      Parameters:
      filePath - filepath to an AIFC, AIFF, AU, SND and WAVE file, a string.
      Throws:
      java.lang.IllegalStateException - if there is a problem opening the audio file.

    • manuallySetSunrise

      void manuallySetSunrise​(int hour, int minute)
      Manually set the start time. Hour should be in 24hr time.
      Parameters:
      hour - the sunrise hour, an int, that is greater than or equal to 0 and less than 24.
      minute - the sunrise minute, an int, that is greater than or equal to 0 and less than 60.
      Throws:
      java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if hour or minute values are less than zero, if hour value is greater than 24, and if minute value is greater than 60.

    • automaticallySetSunrise

      void automaticallySetSunrise​(double latitude, double longitude)
      Automatically sets sunrise when passed a given longitude and latitude. Sunrise data is retrieved from https://sunrise-sunset.org/api, which is parsed using the SunriseSunsetParser.
      Parameters:
      latitude - latitude of the location, a double
      longitude - longitude of the location, a double.

    • setSoundDuration

      void setSoundDuration​(int hour, int minute) throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
      Set length of time that sound should play after the start time.
      Parameters:
      hour - the number of hours the sound should play, a double.
      minute - the number of minutes the sound should play, a double.
      Throws:
      java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if hour or minute values are less than zero
